# State Architecture — `FlowChart.tsx`

## State Shape
```
workspace: WorkspaceDoc          ← single source of truth
activeFactoryId: string          ← which factory tab is open
```
`activeFactory = workspace.factories.find(id === activeFactoryId)`  
`tree = activeFactory.tree`

## Quick Build Mode
- `quickBuildAsFactory: boolean` controls whether Quick Build replaces the active factory tree or creates a new factory tab from the selected recipe.

## Delete Confirm State
- `deleteConfirm` in `FlowChart.tsx` drives a styled confirm modal for destructive actions (delete workspace / delete factory).
- Destructive menu/tab actions should set `deleteConfirm` first; actual delete handlers run only from modal confirm.

## Updating State

**`setWorkspace(updaterOrValue)`** — use for ALL edits the user should be able to undo.  
Pushes the previous workspace onto `pastRef` (max 50) and clears `futureRef`.

**`resetWorkspace(ws)`** — use ONLY for boot/load/new-workspace/save-as.  
Clears history stacks entirely.

**`updateActiveFactory(updater)`** — calls `setWorkspace` internally; updates only the active factory.

**`setTree(updaterOrValue)`** — calls `updateActiveFactory`; updates only `activeFactory.tree`.

## Standard Tree Mutation Pattern
```ts
setTree((t) => recalcTree(synthesizeMissingInputEdges(/* mutation */)));
```
Always wrap tree changes with `synthesizeMissingInputEdges` then `recalcTree`.

When adding a new machine, immediately apply `preferredBeltKey` to the new child incoming belt and all of its input edges (including synthesized ones) before optional auto-balance.

## Undo / Redo
- Stacks: `pastRef: useRef<WorkspaceDoc[]>`, `futureRef: useRef<WorkspaceDoc[]>`
- `historyVersion` state is bumped to re-render undo/redo buttons
- `canUndo = pastRef.current.length > 0`, `canRedo = futureRef.current.length > 0`
- Keyboard: Ctrl/Cmd+Z (undo), Ctrl/Cmd+Y or Ctrl/Cmd+Shift+Z (redo)
- Skipped when focus is in `INPUT`, `TEXTAREA`, or `contentEditable`

## Derived State
```ts
flowRates = useMemo(() => computeFlowRates(tree, importSupply), [tree, importSupply])
importSupply = useMemo(() => getImportSupply(activeFactory), [activeFactory])
```
